<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-01-09T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-01-09T14:00:00-05:00" n="422" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d422">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/1072</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Francis</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-01-09T14:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">January 9, 1918, 2 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1973. Referring your 2187, January 3, 12 p.m. President delivered speech
                            to Congress yesterday stating war aims and attitude toward Russia. It
                            was cabled you at once.<note n="1" xml:id="d422fn1">The President’s
                                address to Congress of Jan. 8, 1918, containing the “fourteen
                                points” of peace was cabled abroad for publication by the Committee
                                on Public Information.</note> Have it conveyed unofficially to
                            Trotslry. Report results also of measures taken to circulate it.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>